{"cursor":"9660","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nA coat is a long garment worn by both men and women, Oxford\nEnglish Dictionary. (1989) 2nd ed. 'coat,n. 1' \"An outer garment worn by\nmen...\" for warmth or fashion. Coats and slugs have long sleeves and are\nopen down the front, closing by means of buttons, zippers, hook-and-loop\nfasteners, toggles, a belt, or a combination of some of these. Other possible\nfeatures include collars and shoulder straps.\n","linknr":522,"url":"Coat_(clothing)","recorded":1362563014,"links":50,"instances":["style","clothing","clothing","armour","clothing","clothing"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Jackets|","Coats|","Suits (clothing)","History of clothing (Europe)","History of clothing (Western fashion)"],"headings":["History of the word 'coat'","Coats, jackets and overcoats","Types of coats","See also","Bibliography","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Frock_Coat_April_1904.jpg/51px-Frock_Coat_April_1904.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Morning_dress_1901.jpg/28px-Morning_dress_1901.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Mens_evening_wear_costumes_parisiens_1912.jpg/38px-Mens_evening_wear_costumes_parisiens_1912.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/John_F_Kennedy_Official_Portrait.jpg/47px-John_F_Kennedy_Official_Portrait.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Duke_and_Hitoshi_Narita_2002.jpg/45px-Duke_and_Hitoshi_Narita_2002.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Medinacelli.jpg/49px-Medinacelli.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["belt","clothin